    <item>
      <title>What</title>
      <link>http://traefik.github.io/post/what/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 11 Sep 2015 00:40:46 +0200</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://traefik.github.io/post/what/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Træfɪk is a modern HTTP reverse proxy and load balancer made to deploy microservices with ease.
It supports several backends (Docker, Mesos/Marathon, Consul, Etcd, Rest API, file&amp;hellip;) to manage its configuration automatically and dynamically (hot-reload).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://raw.githubusercontent.com/EmileVauge/traefik/master/docs/img/backends.png&#34; alt=&#34;Backends&#34; title=&#34;Backends&#34; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Features</title>
      <link>http://traefik.github.io/post/features/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 11 Sep 2015 00:41:40 +0200</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://traefik.github.io/post/features/</guid>
      <description>&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;No dependency hell, single binary made with go&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Simple json Rest API&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Simple TOML file configuration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Multiple backends supported: Docker, Mesos/Marathon, Consul, Etcd, and more to come&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Watchers for backends, can listen change in backends to apply a new configuration automatically&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hot-reloading of configuration. No need to restart the process&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Graceful shutdown http connections during hot-reloads&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Rest Metrics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Tiny docker image included&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;SSL backends support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;SSL frontend support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Get it</title>
      <link>http://traefik.github.io/post/getit/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 11 Sep 2015 00:41:21 +0200</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://traefik.github.io/post/getit/</guid>
      <description>&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The simple way: grab the latest binary from &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/emilevauge/traefik/releases&#34;&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://img.shields.io/github/downloads/EmileVauge/traefik/latest/total.svg&#34; alt=&#34;the Github releases page&#34; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and just run it with the sample configuration file:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;./traefik traefik.toml
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use the tiny Docker image:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;docker run -d -p 8080:8080 -p 80:80 -v $PWD/traefik.toml:/traefik.toml emilevauge/traefik
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;From sources:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;git clone https://github.com/EmileVauge/traefik
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

